about.description:
Biome is a performant toolchain for web projects, it aims to provide developer tools to maintain the health of said projects.
Biome is a fast formatter for JavaScript, TypeScript, JSX, and JSON that scores 97% compatibility with Prettier.
Biome is a performant linter for JavaScript, TypeScript, and JSX that features more than 200 rules from ESLint, typescript-eslint, and other sources.
It outputs detailed and contextualized diagnostics that help you to improve your code and become a better programmer!
Biome is designed from the start to be used interactively within an editor.
It can format and lint malformed code as you are writing it.
about.summary:
A toolchain for web projects, aimed to provide functionalities to maintain them.
Biome offers formatter and linter, usable via CLI and LSP.

raw_meta_yaml:
schema_version: 1

context:
  name: biome
  version: "2.3.13"
  library_prefix: ${{ "${PREFIX}" if unix else "%LIBRARY_PREFIX%" }}

package:
  name: ${{ name|lower }}
  version: ${{ version }}

source:
  url: https://github.com/biomejs/${{ name }}/archive/refs/tags/@biomejs/biome@${{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 8daeeb9e0550ebd10364dc6f990e6f321ac1f25d955317cd6da4813e920e498b

build:
  number: 0
  script:
    env:
      BIOME_VERSION: ${{ version }}
      # Reduce parallelism to reduce max memory usage
      CARGO_BUILD_JOBS: ${{ "1" if env.exists("CI") else "-1" }}
      CARGO_PROFILE_RELEASE_LTO: ${{ "thin" if unix else "no" }}
    content:
      - if: unix
        then: export CARGO_BUILD_RUSTFLAGS="${CARGO_BUILD_RUSTFLAGS} -C strip=symbols"
        else: set CARGO_BUILD_RUSTFLAGS=%CARGO_BUILD_RUSTFLAGS% -C strip=symbols
      - cargo-bundle-licenses --format yaml --output THIRDPARTY.yml
      - cargo install --locked --root "${{ library_prefix }}" --path crates/biome_cli -v

requirements:
  build:
    - ${{ compiler('rust') }}
    - ${{ compiler('c') }}
    - ${{ stdlib('c') }}
    - make
    - cargo-bundle-licenses
  host:
    - if: osx
      then: libiconv

tests:
  - script:
      - biome --version

about:
  summary: |
    A toolchain for web projects, aimed to provide functionalities to maintain them.
    Biome offers formatter and linter, usable via CLI and LSP.
  description: |
    Biome is a performant toolchain for web projects, it aims to provide developer tools to maintain the health of said projects.
    Biome is a fast formatter for JavaScript, TypeScript, JSX, and JSON that scores 97% compatibility with Prettier.
    Biome is a performant linter for JavaScript, TypeScript, and JSX that features more than 200 rules from ESLint, typescript-eslint, and other sources.
    It outputs detailed and contextualized diagnostics that help you to improve your code and become a better programmer!
    Biome is designed from the start to be used interactively within an editor.
    It can format and lint malformed code as you are writing it.
  license: MIT
  license_file:
    - LICENSE-MIT
    - THIRDPARTY.yml
  homepage: https://biomejs.dev
  repository: https://github.com/biomejs/biome
  documentation: https://biomejs.dev/guides/getting-started/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - AntoinePrv
